Product Version     25.10    Cadence Design Systems, Inc.
setFPlanRowSpacingAndType(25.10)              setFPlanRowSpacingAndType(25.10)

Name
       setFPlanRowSpacingAndType  -  Specifies the standard row spacing values
       and row pattern type

Syntax
        setFPlanRowSpacingAndType

       [-help]

       spacing

       type

       Specifies the standard row spacing values and row pattern type. You can
       use this command after importing the design.

Parameters
       -help  Outputs a brief description that includes the type  and  default
              information  for each setFPlanRowSpacingAndType parameter. For a
              detailed description of the command and all of  its  parameters,
              use the man command:

              man setFPlanRowSpacingAndType

       <spacing>
              Specifies the standard row spacing, in micrometers. This must be
              a positive value.

              Default: 0

              Data_type: float, required

       <type> Specifies  the  row  spacing type. Specify 1 for every row, or 2
              for every other row to apply the spacing value.

              Data_type: int, required

Example
       The following command specifies a row spacing value of 1.1  micrometers
       for every other row:

       setFPlanRowSpacingAndType 1.1 2

Related Information
              * Floorplanning the Design chapter in the Innovus User Guide

